article.description: Logan McIntosh scored 13 points Monday night and hit two free throws with 6.4 seconds left to help Maryland-Eastern Shore end a seven-game skid 62-61 over Florida A&M.
article.headline: UMES ends 7-game skid, beats Florida A&M 62-61
article.linkText: UMES ends 7-game skid, beats Florida A&M 62-61
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. -- Logan McIntosh scored 13 points Monday night and hit two free throws with 6.4 seconds left to help Maryland-Eastern Shore end a seven-game skid 62-61 over Florida A&M. Ahmad Frost led the Hawks (6-19, 2-8 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) with 19 points and Miryne Thomas had 16 points and 11 rebounds. UMES trailed 57-52 before Frost hit a 3-pointer with 3:10 left that sparked a 10-4 run to close the game. McIntosh's 3-point play with two minutes to go made it 58-57. The Rattlers retook the lead on Marcus Barham's layup and Desmond Williams' free throw made it 60-58. Thomas tied it with a jumper with 53 seconds left and Williams made another free throw with 29 seconds left before McIntosh's foul shots sealed it. Williams and Justin Ravenel had 17 points each to lead Florida A&M (4-22, 3-7), which has lost four straight. Barham added 15.
